===Etymology===
Old English [[feter]] ''noun'', [[gefeterian|ġefeterian]] ''verb''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|fetter|fetters}}

#A [[chain]] or similar [[object]] used to [[bind]] a person or [[animal]] by its [[leg]]s ''(usually in plural)''.
#(''metaphorical'') Anything that [[restrict]]s or [[restrain]]s in any way.

